def: A close, or inclosure; a croft. [Obs.] Cowell.
A measure of area, or superficies, containing a hundred ares,or 10,000 square meters, and equivalent to 2.471 acres.
Pertaining to, or resembling, an amphora.
The quality of being alimentary; nourishing quality. [R.]
To end up; to set on end, as a cask.
In an inexorable manner; inflexibly. "Inexorably firm."Thomson.
Made or derived from oxalic acid; as, desoxalic acid.
Criminal; involving great crime or grave charges; very wicked;heinous. [Obs.] Holland.-- Crim"i*nous*ly, adv..-- Crim"i*nous*ness,n. [Obs.]
Eating raw flesh; using uncooked meat as food; as, omophagicfeasts, rites.
